question: What is the FY2019 cash conversion cycle (CCC) for General Mills? CCC is defined as: DIO + DSO - DPO. DIO is defined as: 365 * (average inventory between FY2018 and FY2019) / (FY2019 COGS). FY2019 COGS: $11,108.4 million
DIO (Days Inventory Outstanding): (365 * $1,595.75 million) / $11,108.4 million = 54.13 days

Average accounts receivable between FY2018 and FY2019: ($1,679.7 million + $1,684.2 million) / 2 = $1,681.95 million
